    "response_text": "Across the 33 time steps of the simulation, the cumulative count of milk choices made by the consumer population increases linearly from 0 to 32,000. At each successive time step, exactly 1,000 additional choices are accumulated, reflecting consistent decision-making activity across the entire population of 1,000 agents throughout the simulation period. This uniform accumulation rate of 1,000 choices per step indicates that every agent participates in making a milk selection at every time step without dropout or interruption. By the final time step (step 32), the aggregate reaches 32,000 total choices, representing 32 full cycles of population-wide decision-making. The perfectly linear trajectory yields a mean value of 16,000 choices across all time steps, with statistical analysis confirming a consistent slope of 1,000 choices per step (p = 0.027) across all examined intervals of the time series."
}

